{"TopicId":70772,"ForumId":18,"TopicTitle":"A strange idea: Classic Games Pack","CreatedByName":"Javster","CreatedById":74613,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-04-27T20:18:58Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Javster","CreatedById":74613,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-04-27T20:18:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI had a weird idea: a pack of \u0022classic\u0022 games voted on regularly/appointed by a committee, sold for a slightly discounted price. Examples would include Portal, Minecraft etc.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe main idea would be to avoid something I get a lot: \u0022You haven\u0027t played X?\u0022\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOne of the main drawbacks would be developer willingness to contribute to the project, the definition of \u0022classic\u0022, and the overall price of this package.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"vger","CreatedById":67603,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-04-27T22:11:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIt\u0027s been done with games from the 80\u0027s and 90\u0027s. I see no reason why it won\u0027t be done with current games a decade or so from now.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dispatcher","CreatedById":78707,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-04-27T22:53:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EAh, \u00C3\u00A2\u00E2\u201A\u00AC\u00C5\u201CClassic\u00C3\u00A2\u00E2\u201A\u00AC\u00C2 games. Spoiler videos, with a twist, ahead:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022459\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/XNRx5hc4gYc?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E,\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022480\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/sO1jp-0Q4Zw?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allo